    <!-- Start of Philosophy -->
    <div class="container marketing">
	<center><b><h1> Our Philosophy </h1></b></center>
    <br>
	<p>
	In the CBL, we look for ways to combine the advantage of data-driven learning with physics-based modeling, with a goal to bridge the gap between the knowledge in 
	domain physics and the information in large amount of data.	Under this philosophy, the research focus of CBL is two-fold: (1) we develop foundational methods, 
	algorithms, and software to support the integration of physics-based computational simulation and data-driven learning and inference methods for improved 
	investigation of individualized systems; and (2) we are interested in the application of these methods to biomedical problems of importance to public health, 
	especially to improve patient care in cardiac arrhythmia and other heart diseases.
	</p>
	<!-- End of Lab Philosophy -->
	
	
	<!-- Start of Current Projects -->	
	<hr class="featurette-divider">
	<center> <b><h1> Current Projects </h1></b> </center>
	<br><br>
	
	<!-- Start of Row 1 -->	
	<div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-6" >
          <img class="img-rounded" src="images/uncertainty.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="180">
          <h2>Integrating Physical Models into Data-Driven Inference</h2>
          <p align="justify" style="height: 100px;"> An NSF CAREER grant has been awarded to the CBL to develop theoretical and software infrastructure that will 
          support the integration of physics-based computational simulation and data-driven inference methods to improve individualized assessment of systems.</p> 
          <p> <a class="btn btn-default" href="career_page.html" role="button">View details »</a></p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="col-lg-6">
          <img class="img-rounded" src="images/tepi.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="180">
          <h2>Noninvasive Transmural Electrophysiological Imaging</h2>
          <p align="justify">This work, funded by a NIH R21 grant, focuses on the clinical value of TEPI in mapping both the electrophysiological substrate and 
          arrhythmia dynamics in patients with scar-related ventricular arrhythmia. By providing improved pre-procedural targeting, TEPI has the potential to 
          improve the efficiency and efficacy of catheter ablation as a pre-procedural planning tool.</p>
          <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="tepi.html" role="button" >View details »</a></p>
        </div>
   </div>
   <!-- End of Row 1 -->
	<br>

	<!-- Start of Row 2 -->
	<div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-6">
          <img class="img-rounded" src="images/HMC2.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="180">
          <h2>Data Inversion of Complex Physical Systems</h2>
          <p align="justify">To combine mechanistic knowledge of domain physics provided by computational models and specific information of individual systems 
          provided by measurement data, parameter estimation for system models is a powerful approach to obtaining a custom model that can not only facilitate 
          the quantitative understanding of an individual system, but also help predict the unseen future. This is particularly important for the personalized 
          diagnosis, treatment, and prevention of diseases in a cardiac.
        	</p>
          <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="Data-Inversion.html" role="button">View details »</a></p>
        </div>
       
        <div class="col-lg-6">
          <img src="images/cbl_logo.svg" alt="" width="300" height="180">
          <h2 style="height: 64.4445px">Integrated Cardiac Imaging & Imaging Genetics</h2>
          <p align="justify">This is an exciting research initiative in the CBL in collaboration with Geisinger Health System (Danville, PA) in an effort to integrate 
          the analysis of patient clinical data (including EHR, ECG, image scans, and other clinical data) and genetic data towards the ultimate goal of precision medicine. 
          </p>
          <br><br>
          <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="Additional.html#iig" role="button">View details »</a></p>
        </div>
	</div>
	<!-- End of Row 2 -->
	<br>

	<!-- Start of Row 3 -->
	<div class="row">
   	<div class="col-lg-6">
         <img src="images/ml_logo.svg" alt="" width="300" height="180">
         <h2 style="height: 64.4445px">Machine Learning for Precision Medicine</h2>
         <p align="justify">Within our general interests in using the power of machine learning algorithms to uncover the knowledge represented within biomedical data, 
          we are particularly interested in the development of learning algorithms to extract and differentiate among factors of different variations within the data. 
          This is especially important in personalized medicine, when one tries to extract diagnostic biomarkers in the presence of variances across patients or other 
          confounding factors. This interest expands to related domains including multi-task learning, domain adaptation, and transfer learning.
        	</p>
         <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="ml_cbl.html" role="button">View details »</a></p>
      </div>    
       
		<div class="col-lg-6" >
            <img class="img-rounded" src="images/Sensor.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="180">
                <h2 style="height: 64.4445px">Multi-Modal Sensor Fusion for Cognitive Monitoring and Stress Detection</h2>
                <p style="height: 160px" align="justify">Software development in the CBL covers multiple aspects including processing tools to facilitate the preparation of raw experimental and clinical data, such as the processing of multi-lead ECG data and geometrical modeling tools using homographic scans, as well as GPU based acceleration of data-driven modeling and inference algorithms developed in the lab. </p>
                <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="Additional.html#sensor" role="button">View details »</a></p>
   	</div>
	</div>
	<!-- End of Row 3 -->
   <br>
   
   <!-- Start of Row 4 -->
	<div class="row">
       <div class="col-lg-6" >
       	<img class="img-rounded" src="images/Sofware_pic.png" alt="" width="300" height="180">
         <h2 style="height: 64.4445px">Software Development</h2>
         <p style="height: 120px" align="justify">Software development in the CBL covers multiple aspects including processing tools to facilitate the preparation of raw experimental and clinical data, such as the processing of multi-lead ECG data and geometrical modeling tools using homographic scans, as well as GPU based acceleration of data-driven modeling and inference algorithms developed in the lab. </p>
         <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="software.html" role="button">View details »</a></p>
